<headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 24 at 8:14PM CDT  by NWS Shreveport</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT SOUTHWESTERN FRANKLIN...WOOD AND
WEST CENTRAL UPSHUR COUNTIES THROUGH 845 PM CDT...
At 814 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Lake Fork Reservoir, or 13 miles northwest of Mineola, moving south
at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Mineola, Winnsboro, Quitman, Lake Fork Reservoir, Pleasant Grove,
Hainesville, Golden, Forest Hill, Alba, Yantis, and Perryville.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...55 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
